  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e49f1e0d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# ChatGithubCopilot\n",
    "\n",
    "This will help you get started with GitHub Copilot [chat models](/docs/concepts/chat_models) via the [GitHub Models inference API](https://docs.github.com/en/rest/models/inference). For detailed documentation of all `ChatGithubCopilot` features and configurations head to the [API reference](https://python.langchain.com/api_reference/githubcopilot_chat/chat_models/langchain_githubcopilot_chat.chat_models.ChatGithubCopilot.html).\n",
    "\n",
    "GitHub Models gives you access to leading AI models — including OpenAI GPT-4.1, Meta Llama 3.3, DeepSeek, Microsoft Phi, Mistral, and more — through a single, unified REST API endpoint at `https://models.github.ai`. Authentication is handled entirely with a GitHub personal access token (PAT), so there is no extra account setup required if you already have a GitHub account.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "### Integration details\n",
    "\n",
    "| Class | Package | Local | Serializable | JS support | Package downloads | Package latest |\n",
    "| :--- | :--- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |\n",
    "| [ChatGithubCopilot](https://python.langchain.com/api_reference/githubcopilot_chat/chat_models/langchain_githubcopilot_chat.chat_models.ChatGithubCopilot.html) | [langchain-githubcopilot-chat](https://pypi.org/project/langchain-githubcopilot-chat/) | ❌ | beta | ❌ | ![PyPI - Downloads](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/langchain-githubcopilot-chat?style=flat-square&label=%20) | ![PyPI - Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/langchain-githubcopilot-chat?style=flat-square&label=%20) |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Model features\n",
    "\n",
    "| [Tool calling](/docs/how_to/tool_calling) | [Structured output](/docs/how_to/structured_output/) | JSON mode | [Image input](/docs/how_to/multimodal_inputs/) | Audio input | Video input | [Token-level streaming](/docs/how_to/chat_streaming/) | Native async | [Token usage](/docs/how_to/chat_token_usage_tracking/) | Logprobs |\n",
    "| :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |\n",
    "| ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ |\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Note:** Image input and multimodal capabilities depend on the specific model chosen. Models like `openai/gpt-4.1` support image inputs; text-only models do not.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "### Credentials\n",
    "\n",
    "To use GitHub Models you need a GitHub account and a **personal access token (PAT)**.\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Go to [github.com/settings/tokens](https://github.com/settings/tokens) and create a new **fine-grained PAT** (or a classic token).\n",
    "2. For fine-grained tokens, grant the **`models: read`** permission under *Account permissions*.\n",
    "3. Copy the token and set it as the `GITHUB_TOKEN` environment variable.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **GitHub Copilot subscribers** can also use their Copilot-issued token directly — the same `GITHUB_TOKEN` env-var is used.\n",
    "\n",
    "You can explore available models at the [GitHub Marketplace Models page](https://github.com/marketplace/models)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "433e8d2b-9519-4b49-b2c4-7ab65b046c94",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import getpass\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "if not os.getenv(\"GITHUB_TOKEN\"):\n",
    "    os.environ[\"GITHUB_TOKEN\"] = getpass.getpass(\"Enter your GitHub token: \")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
