    "# os.environ[\"LANGSMITH_API_KEY\"] = getpass.getpass(\"Enter your LangSmith API key: \")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0730d6a1-c893-4840-9817-5e5251676d5d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Installation\n",
    "\n",
    "The LangChain GitHub Copilot integration lives in the `langchain-githubcopilot-chat` package:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "652d6238-1f87-422a-b135-f5abbb8652fc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%pip install -qU langchain-githubcopilot-chat"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a38cde65-254d-4219-a441-068766c0d4b5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Instantiation\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we can instantiate our model object. The model ID follows the `{publisher}/{model_name}` format. You can browse all available models with:\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "curl -H \"Authorization: Bearer $GITHUB_TOKEN\" \\\n",
    "     -H \"X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2026-03-10\" \\\n",
    "     https://models.github.ai/catalog/models\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Some popular model IDs:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Model | ID |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| OpenAI GPT-4.1 | `openai/gpt-4.1` |\n",
    "| OpenAI GPT-4.1 mini | `openai/gpt-4.1-mini` |\n",
    "| OpenAI GPT-4o | `openai/gpt-4o` |\n",
    "| Meta Llama 3.3 70B | `meta/llama-3.3-70b-instruct` |\n",
    "| DeepSeek R1 | `deepseek/deepseek-r1` |\n",
    "| Microsoft Phi-4 | `microsoft/phi-4` |\n",
    "| Mistral Small | `mistral-ai/mistral-small` |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cb09c344-1836-4e0c-acf8-11d13ac1dbae",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from langchain_githubcopilot_chat import ChatGithubCopilot\n",
    "\n",
    "llm = ChatGithubCopilot(\n",
    "    model=\"openai/gpt-4.1\",\n",
    "    temperature=0,\n",
    "    max_tokens=1024,\n",
    "    # github_token=\"github_pat_...\",  # or set GITHUB_TOKEN env var\n",
    "    # org=\"my-org\",                   # optional: attribute requests to an org\n",
    "    # timeout=30.0,                   # optional: request timeout in seconds\n",
    "    # max_retries=2,                  # optional: number of retries on transient errors\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2b4f3e15",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Invocation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "62e0dbc3",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "messages = [\n",
    "    (\n",
    "        \"system\",\n",
    "        \"You are a helpful assistant that translates English to French. Translate the user sentence.\",\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    (\"human\", \"I love programming.\"),\n",
    "]\n",
    "ai_msg = llm.invoke(messages)\n",
    "ai_msg"
   ]
  },
  {
