   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "18e2bfc0-7e78-4528-a73f-499ac150dca8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Chaining\n",
    "\n",
    "We can [chain](/docs/how_to/sequence/) our model with a prompt template like so:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e197d1d7-a070-4c96-9f8a-a0e86d046e0b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\n",
    "\n",
    "prompt = ChatPromptTemplate(\n",
    "    [\n",
    "        (\n",
    "            \"system\",\n",
    "            \"You are a helpful assistant that translates {input_language} to {output_language}.\",\n",
    "        ),\n",
    "        (\"human\", \"{input}\"),\n",
    "    ]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "chain = prompt | llm\n",
    "chain.invoke(\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        \"input_language\": \"English\",\n",
    "        \"output_language\": \"German\",\n",
    "        \"input\": \"I love programming.\",\n",
    "    }\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "output-chain",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```\n",
    "AIMessage(\n",
    "    content='Ich liebe das Programmieren.',\n",
    "    additional_kwargs={},\n",
    "    response_metadata={'finish_reason': 'stop', 'usage': {'prompt_tokens': 26, 'completion_tokens': 7, 'total_tokens': 33}},\n",
    "    usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 26, 'output_tokens': 7, 'total_tokens': 33}\n",
    ")\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "streaming-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Streaming\n",
    "\n",
    "`ChatGithubCopilot` supports token-level streaming for all models that expose Server-Sent Events (SSE) in the GitHub Models API."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "stream-sync",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "messages = [\n",
    "    (\"system\", \"You are a concise assistant.\"),\n",
    "    (\"human\", \"Write a haiku about open-source software.\"),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "for chunk in llm.stream(messages):\n",
    "    print(chunk.content, end=\"\", flush=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "output-stream",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```\n",
    "Code shared freely,\n",
    "Community builds the dream—\n",
    "All may read the source.\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "async-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Async support\n",
    "\n",
    "`ChatGithubCopilot` implements native async versions of both `_agenerate` and `_astream` using `httpx.AsyncClient`, so it works cleanly in async frameworks like FastAPI or Jupyter notebooks with `asyncio`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "async-invoke",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ai_msg = await llm.ainvoke(messages)\n",
    "print(ai_msg.content)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "async-stream",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "async for chunk in llm.astream(messages):\n",
    "    print(chunk.content, end=\"\", flush=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "tool-calling-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Tool calling\n",
    "\n",
    "GitHub Models supports the OpenAI-compatible `tools` / `tool_calls` interface. Pass tools using `bind_tools()` and the model will return structured `tool_calls` in the response when appropriate."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "tool-calling-basic",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pydantic import BaseModel, Field\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class GetWeather(BaseModel):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Get the current weather for a given location.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    location: str = Field(..., description=\"City and country, e.g. 'Paris, France'\")\n",
    "    unit: str = Field(default=\"celsius\", description=\"Temperature unit: 'celsius' or 'fahrenheit'\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class GetPopulation(BaseModel):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Get the current population of a city.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    city: str = Field(..., description=\"Name of the city\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "llm_with_tools = llm.bind_tools([GetWeather, GetPopulation])\n",
    "\n",
    "ai_msg = llm_with_tools.invoke(\n",
    "    \"What is the weather like in Tokyo and what is its population?\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ai_msg.tool_calls"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "output-tool-calls",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```python\n",
    "[\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        'name': 'GetWeather',\n",
    "        'args': {'location': 'Tokyo, Japan', 'unit': 'celsius'},\n",
    "        'id': 'call_abc123',\n",
    "        'type': 'tool_call'\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        'name': 'GetPopulation',\n",
    "        'args': {'city': 'Tokyo'},\n",
    "        'id': 'call_def456',\n",
    "        'type': 'tool_call'\n",
    "    }\n",
    "]\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "tool-choice-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "You can also force a specific tool choice:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "tool-choice",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Force the model to always call a tool\n",
    "llm_required_tools = llm.bind_tools([GetWeather], tool_choice=\"required\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Force the model to never call tools (plain text response)\n",
    "llm_no_tools = llm.bind_tools([GetWeather], tool_choice=\"none\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "tool-calling-agent-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Full tool-calling loop\n",
    "\n",
    "Here is a complete example of a tool-calling loop that processes tool call results and sends them back to the model:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "tool-calling-loop",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from langchain_core.messages import AIMessage, HumanMessage, ToolMessage\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_weather(location: str, unit: str = \"celsius\") -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Simulated weather tool.\"\"\"\n",
    "    return f\"The weather in {location} is 22°{unit[0].upper()} and sunny.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_population(city: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Simulated population tool.\"\"\"\n",
    "    populations = {\"Tokyo\": \"13.96 million\", \"Paris\": \"2.16 million\"}\n",
    "    return f\"The population of {city} is approximately {populations.get(city, 'unknown')}.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "tool_map = {\"GetWeather\": get_weather, \"GetPopulation\": get_population}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 1: initial invocation\n",
    "messages = [HumanMessage(\"What is the weather in Tokyo, and what is its population?\")]\n",
    "ai_msg = llm_with_tools.invoke(messages)\n",
    "messages.append(ai_msg)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 2: execute each requested tool call\n",
    "for tc in ai_msg.tool_calls:\n",
    "    tool_fn = tool_map[tc[\"name\"]]\n",
    "    result = tool_fn(**tc[\"args\"])\n",
    "    messages.append(ToolMessage(content=result, tool_call_id=tc[\"id\"]))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 3: send tool results back for a final answer\n",
    "final_msg = llm_with_tools.invoke(messages)\n",
    "print(final_msg.content)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "output-tool-loop",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```\n",
    "In Tokyo, the current weather is 22°C and sunny. The population of Tokyo is approximately 13.96 million people.\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "structured-output-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Structured output\n",
    "\n",
    "`ChatGithubCopilot` supports `with_structured_output()` to reliably extract structured data conforming to a Pydantic model or JSON schema. It is implemented via tool-calling under the hood."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "structured-output",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from typing import List, Optional\n",
    "\n",
    "from pydantic import BaseModel, Field\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class MovieReview(BaseModel):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Structured movie review.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    title: str = Field(description=\"The title of the movie\")\n",
    "    year: int = Field(description=\"The release year of the movie\")\n",
    "    rating: float = Field(description=\"Rating out of 10\")\n",
    "    pros: List[str] = Field(description=\"Positive aspects of the movie\")\n",
    "    cons: List[str] = Field(description=\"Negative aspects of the movie\")\n",
    "    summary: str = Field(description=\"One-sentence summary of the review\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "structured_llm = llm.with_structured_output(MovieReview)\n",
    "\n",
    "result = structured_llm.invoke(\n",
    "    \"Review the movie Inception by Christopher Nolan.\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "result"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "output-structured",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```python\n",
    "MovieReview(\n",
    "    title='Inception',\n",
    "    year=2010,\n",
    "    rating=9.0,\n",
    "    pros=['Mind-bending plot', 'Stunning visuals', 'Outstanding performances', 'Innovative concept'],\n",
    "    cons=['Complex narrative may confuse some viewers', 'Emotional depth could be greater'],\n",
    "    summary='A visually spectacular and intellectually stimulating sci-fi thriller that pushes the boundaries of filmmaking.'\n",
    ")\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "json-mode-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## JSON mode\n",
    "\n",
    "Use `response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"}` to make the model return a valid JSON object. The model will always output parseable JSON when this mode is enabled."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "json-mode",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "\n",
    "json_llm = llm.bind(response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"})\n",
    "\n",
    "ai_msg = json_llm.invoke(\n",
    "    [\n",
    "        (\"system\", \"You are a helpful assistant. Always respond with valid JSON.\"),\n",
    "        (\n",
    "            \"human\",\n",
    "            \"Return a JSON object with key 'languages' containing a list of the 5 most popular programming languages and their paradigms.\",\n",
    "        ),\n",
    "    ]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "data = json.loads(ai_msg.content)\n",
    "data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "output-json-mode",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```python\n",
    "{\n",
    "    'languages': [\n",
    "        {'name': 'Python',     'paradigms': ['object-oriented', 'functional', 'imperative']},\n",
    "        {'name': 'JavaScript', 'paradigms': ['event-driven', 'functional', 'object-oriented']},\n",
    "        {'name': 'Java',       'paradigms': ['object-oriented', 'imperative']},\n",
    "        {'name': 'C++',        'paradigms': ['object-oriented', 'procedural', 'generic']},\n",
    "        {'name': 'Rust',       'paradigms': ['systems', 'functional', 'concurrent']}\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "}\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "image-input-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Image input (multimodal)\n",
    "\n",
    "Models that support multimodal input (e.g. `openai/gpt-4.1`, `openai/gpt-4o`) can accept images alongside text. Pass an image as a base64-encoded data URL inside a `HumanMessage` with a list of content blocks."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "image-input",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import base64\n",
    "\n",
    "import httpx\n",
    "from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage\n",
    "\n",
    "# Download a sample image\n",
    "image_url = \"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dd/Gfp-wisconsin-madison-the-nature-boardwalk.jpg/640px-Gfp-wisconsin-madison-the-nature-boardwalk.jpg\"\n",
    "image_data = base64.b64encode(httpx.get(image_url).content).decode(\"utf-8\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use a multimodal model\n",
    "vision_llm = ChatGithubCopilot(model=\"openai/gpt-4.1\", max_tokens=256)\n",
    "\n",
    "message = HumanMessage(\n",
    "    content=[\n",
    "        {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Describe the scene in this image in one sentence.\"},\n",
    "        {\n",
    "            \"type\": \"image_url\",\n",
    "            \"image_url\": {\"url\": f\"data:image/jpeg;base64,{image_data}\"},\n",
    "        },\n",
    "    ]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "ai_msg = vision_llm.invoke([message])\n",
    "print(ai_msg.content)"
   ]
  },
